Lots of nice detail as well.<p>In the house of code one the protagonist is writing up the HeartBeatMessage class from the bouncycastle tls library: <a href="https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java/blob/master/core/src/main/java/org/bouncycastle/crypto/tls/HeartbeatMessage.java" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java/blob/master/core/src/main/j...</a><p>in the Breaking Bad one has some java code that evaluates to his name on the tablet.<p><pre><code>    public class JavaDoc {
      public String name() {
        return asList(&#x27;I&#x27;, &#x27;x&#x27;,
                      &#x27;`&#x27;, &#x27;u&#x27;,
                      &#x27;`&#x27;, &#x27;a&#x27;,
                      &#x27;x&#x27;, &#x27;d&#x27;,
                      &#x27;q&#x27;, &#x27;f&#x27;)
                      .stream()
                      .filter(c -> c != 120)
                      .map(c -> (char) (c + 1))
                      .map(c -> &quot;&quot; + c)
                      .reduce((a, b) -> a + b)
                      .get();
      }
    }
</code></pre>
